 between MD and experiment are 1-2 orders of magnitude larger than\nthose seen between QHA and MD, so the quality of the force field used is still\nof primary concern, but this study illustrates a number of other important\nfactors that must be considered to obtain quantitative organic crystal\nthermodynamics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Oct 2019 16:41:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-18"}
