ir upper\natmospheres. With an impending UV observation gap and the scarcity of observed\nEUV spectra for stars less luminous and more distant than the Sun,\nupper-atmosphere models such as these are important for providing realistic\nspectra across short wavelengths and for advancing our understanding of the\neffects of radiation on planets orbiting M stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Oct 2019 17:32:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
