dles,\ncalled unit-free configuration spaces, and, they are shown to fit into a theory\nof phase spaces with a Hamiltonian functor given by the jet functor.\n  Motivated by the algebraic structure of physical quantities in dimensional\nanalysis, we define dimensioned groups, rings, modules and algebras by\nimplementing an addition operation that is partially defined. Jacobi manfolds\nare shown to have associated dimensioned Poisson algebras and dimensioned\ncoisotropic calculus.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Oct 2019 15:27:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-21"}
